{"nodes": [{"id": "docs_architecture_reference_patterns_b_design_token_pattern", "label": "Design token pattern (globals.css, class-based dark mode via next-themes)", "file_type": "rationale", "source_file": "docs/architecture/reference-patterns/b-ui-tresci-walidacja.md", "source_location": null, "source_url": null, "captured_at": null, "author": null, "contributor": null, "rationale": "Tokens are HSL triplets under :root with a .dark override, mapped via @theme inline; never reintroduce prefers-color-scheme in components or hard-code a color."}, {"id": "docs_architecture_reference_patterns_b_root_layout_session_read", "label": "Root layout session read / impersonation banner", "file_type": "rationale", "source_file": "docs/architecture/reference-patterns/b-ui-tresci-walidacja.md", "source_location": null, "source_url": null, "captured_at": null, "author": null, "contributor": null, "rationale": "getServerSession() in the root layout opts every page into dynamic rendering; the impersonation banner lives there because it must cover forbidden.tsx, /login and the admin group with no gap."}, {"id": "docs_architecture_reference_patterns_b_server_rendered_content_pages", "label": "Server-rendered (not statically generated) content pages", "file_type": "rationale", "source_file": "docs/architecture/reference-patterns/b-ui-tresci-walidacja.md", "source_location": null, "source_url": null, "captured_at": null, "author": null, "contributor": null, "rationale": "Next 16 removed the per-route PPR opt-in (experimental_ppr gone); only cacheComponents remains as an app-wide escape hatch, a phase of its own. Nothing in spec 9.1 requires SSG - only visibility with JS disabled, asserted by e2e/content-no-js.spec.ts. sitemap.ts/robots.ts/opengraph-image routes are still static route handlers."}, {"id": "docs_architecture_reference_patterns_b_content_publishing_registry_pattern", "label": "Publish content pattern (meta.ts + content.mdx + registry index.ts)", "file_type": "rationale", "source_file": "docs/architecture/reference-patterns/b-ui-tresci-walidacja.md", "source_location": null, "source_url": null, "captured_at": null, "author": null, "contributor": null, "rationale": "The registry key is the slug, directory name and URL at once - no separate slug field to disagree with the others. Registry entries are literal specifiers so content is traced by the bundler; never replace with a dynamic import by slug. Drafts are filtered at source.ts unconditionally."}, {"id": "docs_architecture_reference_patterns_b_public_route_pattern", "label": "Add a public route pattern (public-routes.ts, indexable flag, three consumers)", "file_type": "rationale", "source_file": "docs/architecture/reference-patterns/b-ui-tresci-walidacja.md", "source_location": null, "source_url": null, "captured_at": null, "author": null, "contributor": null, "rationale": "One bare-path entry drives proxy.ts, sitemap.ts and robots.ts so reachable and indexed cannot drift apart; a prefix rule on / would turn default-deny into open access."}, {"id": "docs_architecture_reference_patterns_b_page_metadata_pattern", "label": "Page metadata pattern (pageMetadata(), openGraph replace-not-merge)", "file_type": "rationale", "source_file": "docs/architecture/reference-patterns/b-ui-tresci-walidacja.md", "source_location": null, "source_url": null, "captured_at": null, "author": null, "contributor": null, "rationale": "Metadata segments replace openGraph rather than merging; a page setting only title/description silently inherits the root's og:title, so every page must use pageMetadata() and e2e asserts og:title, not just <title>."}, {"id": "docs_architecture_reference_patterns_b_og_image_routes", "label": "OG image routes are public by construction", "file_type": "rationale", "source_file": "docs/architecture/reference-patterns/b-ui-tresci-walidacja.md", "source_location": null, "source_url": null, "captured_at": null, "author": null, "contributor": null, "rationale": "Next serves generated images at an extension-less path with hash in the query, so the proxy's dot-based skip does not apply; isMetadataImageRoute matches the suffix explicitly."}, {"id": "docs_architecture_reference_patterns_b_structured_data_jsonld", "label": "Structured data / JsonLd component (escaped < to prevent stored XSS)", "file_type": "rationale", "source_file": "docs/architecture/reference-patterns/b-ui-tresci-walidacja.md", "source_location": null, "source_url": null, "captured_at": null, "author": null, "contributor": null, "rationale": "JSON.stringify would happily emit </script> from a post title, ending the script element; the < escape in <JsonLd> prevents stored XSS via a blog title."}, {"id": "docs_architecture_reference_patterns_b_prose_styling", "label": "Prose styling pattern (<Prose>, tokens mapped once, no dark:prose-invert)", "file_type": "rationale", "source_file": "docs/architecture/reference-patterns/b-ui-tresci-walidacja.md", "source_location": null, "source_url": null, "captured_at": null, "author": null, "contributor": null, "rationale": "The tokens already flip under .dark, so dark:prose-invert would layer the plugin's own dark palette on top and break it; e2e/content-prose.spec.ts asserts computed colour."}, {"id": "docs_architecture_reference_patterns_b_remark_rehype_plugin", "label": "Remark/rehype plugin constraint (string name + serializable options only)", "file_type": "rationale", "source_file": "docs/architecture/reference-patterns/b-ui-tresci-walidacja.md", "source_location": null, "source_url": null, "captured_at": null, "author": null, "contributor": null, "rationale": "Turbopack passes plugins to a Rust loader so a JS function cannot cross that boundary - which is why there is no syntax highlighter requiring function options."}, {"id": "docs_architecture_reference_patterns_b_confirm_dialog_pattern", "label": "ConfirmDialog pattern (portaled dialog + form id + confirmForm attribute)", "file_type": "rationale", "source_file": "docs/architecture/reference-patterns/b-ui-tresci-walidacja.md", "source_location": null, "source_url": null, "captured_at": null, "author": null, "contributor": null}, {"id": "docs_architecture_reference_patterns_b_server_action_feedback_pattern", "label": "Server action feedback pattern (FormMessage for errors, toast for success)", "file_type": "rationale", "source_file": "docs/architecture/reference-patterns/b-ui-tresci-walidacja.md", "source_location": null, "source_url": null, "captured_at": null, "author": null, "contributor": null}, {"id": "docs_architecture_reference_patterns_b_protected_endpoint_pattern", "label": "Protected endpoint / server action pattern (requireSession() first line)", "file_type": "rationale", "source_file": "docs/architecture/reference-patterns/b-ui-tresci-walidacja.md", "source_location": null, "source_url": null, "captured_at": null, "author": null, "contributor": null}, {"id": "docs_architecture_reference_patterns_b_validation_layer_pattern", "label": "Validation layer pattern (zod at trust boundary, parse-then-authorize)", "file_type": "rationale", "source_file": "docs/architecture/reference-patterns/b-ui-tresci-walidacja.md", "source_location": null, "source_url": null, "captured_at": null, "author": null, "contributor": null, "rationale": "Every value crossing the trust boundary passes a zod schema before business logic; a server action argument is treated as an untrusted input since it is reachable by anyone who can POST the same shape; field errors are suppressed for anti-enumeration paths (sign-in, password reset, unsubscribe)."}, {"id": "docs_architecture_reference_patterns_b_soft_delete_retention_pattern", "label": "Soft delete + retention pattern (deletedAt, structural access revocation)", "file_type": "rationale", "source_file": "docs/architecture/reference-patterns/b-ui-tresci-walidacja.md", "source_location": null, "source_url": null, "captured_at": null, "author": null, "contributor": null, "rationale": "organization, personal_account and user carry deletedAt; a soft-deleted user cannot sign in and live sessions die on next request. The purge job is deferred - organization.createdByUserId is onDelete:restrict, so hard-deleting a user who created an org fails at the FK."}], "edges": [{"source": "docs_architecture_reference_patterns_b_design_token_pattern", "target": "docs_boilerplate_spec_07_system_designu", "relation": "cites", "confidence": "EXTRACTED", "confidence_score": 1.0, "source_file": "docs/architecture/reference-patterns/b-ui-tresci-walidacja.md", "source_location": null, "weight": 1.0}, {"source": "docs_architecture_reference_patterns_b_design_token_pattern", "target": "docs_boilerplate_spec_07_dark_light_theme", "relation": "implements", "confidence": "INFERRED", "confidence_score": 0.85, "source_file": "docs/architecture/reference-patterns/b-ui-tresci-walidacja.md", "source_location": null, "weight": 1.0}, {"source": "docs_architecture_reference_patterns_b_root_layout_session_read", "target": "docs_boilerplate_spec_06_funkcje_panelu", "relation": "cites", "confidence": "EXTRACTED", "confidence_score": 1.0, "source_file": "docs/architecture/reference-patterns/b-ui-tresci-walidacja.md", "source_location": null, "weight": 1.0}, {"source": "docs_architecture_reference_patterns_b_server_rendered_content_pages", "target": "docs_boilerplate_spec_09_wymagania_seo", "relation": "cites", "confidence": "EXTRACTED", "confidence_score": 1.0, "source_file": "docs/architecture/reference-patterns/b-ui-tresci-walidacja.md", "source_location": null, "weight": 1.0}, {"source": "docs_architecture_reference_patterns_b_server_rendered_content_pages", "target": "docs_boilerplate_spec_08_generowanie_stron", "relation": "conceptually_related_to", "confidence": "INFERRED", "confidence_score": 0.85, "source_file": "docs/architecture/reference-patterns/b-ui-tresci-walidacja.md", "source_location": null, "weight": 1.0}, {"source": "docs_architecture_reference_patterns_b_content_publishing_registry_pattern", "target": "